SIMPLE: enlist
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enlist
<hw>En*list"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Enlisted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Enlisting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To enter on a list;
to enroll; to register.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To engage for military or naval service, the name
being entered on a list or register; <as>as, to <ex>enlist</ex>
men</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To secure the support and aid of; to employ in
advancing interest; <as>as, to <ex>enlist</ex> persons in the cause of
truth, or in a charitable enterprise</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enlist</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Enlist
<hw>En*list"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To enroll and bind
one's self for military or naval service; <as>as, he <ex>enlisted</ex>
in the regular army; the men <ex>enlisted</ex> for the
war.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To enter heartily into a cause, as if
enrolled.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>enlisted</ent>⟦br⟧
